<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Arrivly"
  description="How Arrivly handles information when you visit our site. Compliant with the Australian Privacy Act 1988.">

  <article class="prose max-w-[760px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 pt-12 pb-16 sm:pt-20 sm:pb-24">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Arrivly (arrivly.com.au) handles information when you visit our website.</p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>Arrivly is a comparison website for international students in Australia. We are based in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia.</p>
    <p>For privacy questions, contact us at:<br />
      <strong>[YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS]</strong></p>

    <h2>What information we collect</h2>

    <h3>Information you give us</h3>
    <p>We do not require you to create an account or provide personal information to use our comparison tools.</p>
    <p>If you contact us by email, we receive your email address and the content of your message.</p>

    <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
    <p><strong>Analytics</strong><br />
      We use Plausible Analytics to understand how people use our site. Plausible is privacy-friendly — it does not use cookies and does not collect personal data or device identifiers. It is compliant with GDPR, CCPA, and Australian privacy law. See their policy at <a href="https://plausible.io/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plausible.io/privacy</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Affiliate link tracking</strong><br />
      When you click a link to a provider on our site, that provider's affiliate network may place a cookie on your device to track whether you complete a purchase. This is how we earn commissions. The data collected at that point is governed by the provider's privacy policy, not ours.</p>

    <p>Affiliate networks we use include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Commission Factory (commissionfactory.com)</li>
      <li>Direct affiliate programs with individual providers</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <p>We use analytics data only to understand which comparison tools are most useful and to improve the site. We do not use it to identify individuals.</p>
    <p>We do not use your information for marketing without your explicit consent.</p>

    <h2>Who we share information with</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information to anyone.</p>
    <p>We share limited data with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Plausible Analytics (EU-based) — anonymous usage statistics only</li>
      <li>Affiliate networks — only when you click an affiliate link and only the data needed to track that referral</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Overseas disclosure</h2>
    <p>Plausible Analytics is based in the European Union. By using our site, you consent to your anonymous usage data being processed in the EU. The EU maintains privacy standards comparable to Australian law.</p>

    <h2>Your rights under Australian Privacy Law</h2>
    <p>Under the Australian Privacy Act 1988, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Ask what personal information we hold about you</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
      <li>Make a complaint about how we handle your information</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at:<br />
      <strong>[YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS]</strong></p>
    <p>If you are unsatisfied with our response, you may contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oaic.gov.au</a>.</p>

    <h2>Complaints</h2>
    <p>If you have a privacy concern, please contact us first at <strong>[YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS]</strong>. We will respond within 30 days. If unresolved, you may escalate to the OAIC.</p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy. The date at the top shows when it was last changed. Continued use of the site after changes means you accept the updated policy.</p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>This policy is governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia.</p>
  </article>

</BaseLayout>
